```css Style.css
/* Global Styles for BlogPosts */

/* 
**Layout & Responsiveness**
Ensure readability across devices ( phones & computers )
*/
* {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 20px;
  max-width: 800px; /* adjustable maximum width */
  width: 90%; /* responsive width */
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

/* 
**Theme Toggle (Dark/Light)**
Initial theme setup; toggle functionality to be added via JavaScript
*/
:root {
  --text-color: #000; /* default: black text */
  --background-color: #fff; /* default: white background */
  --header-background-color: #f0f0f0; /* light gray for headers */
}

body {
  color: var(--text-color);
  background-color: var(--background-color);
}

/* 
**Visual Distinctions between Sections**
Basic styling for common HTML elements
*/
header, 
footer {
  background-color: var(--header-background-color);
  padding: 1em;
  text-align: center;
}

section > * {
  margin-bottom: 20px; /* spacing between direct children of sections */
}

h1, h2, h3 {
  color: #333; /* slightly darker text for headings */
  margin-top: 0.5em;
  margin-bottom: 0.25em;
}

/* 
**Theme Toggle Classes**
To be applied via JavaScript when the theme button is clicked
*/
.dark-theme {
  --text-color: #fff; /* white text */
  --background-color: #000; /* black background */
  --header-background-color: #333; /* darker gray for headers on dark theme */
}

.light-theme {
  /* No need to redefine, using default :root values */
}
```

**Explanation of Changes and Suggestions:**

* **Global Styles:** Resetting box-sizing and margins/paddings for consistency.
* **Layout & Responsiveness:** Ensuring content is readable by setting a maximum width and making the layout responsive.
* **Theme Toggle (Dark/Light):**
	+ Defined CSS variables (`--text-color`, `--background-color`, `--header-background-color`) for easy theme switching.
	+ Initial setup uses light theme; to activate dark theme, add `.dark-theme` class to `<body>`.
	+ **Next Step:** Integrate a JavaScript toggle button to dynamically apply `.dark-theme` or `.light-theme` classes to the `<body>` element.
* **Visual Distinctions:**
	+ Added basic styling for `header`, `footer`, and sections to enhance readability.

**To Apply These Changes:**

1. You can use the **Apply Button** on this code block (if available) to create a new `Style.css` file with these contents.
2. Alternatively, switch to **Agent Mode** using the Mode Selector dropdown to have the changes applied automatically.
3. After applying, ensure to link the `Style.css` file in the `<head>` section of each HTML file in your BlogPosts folder for the styles to take effect.

**Example `<link>` Tag for Each HTML File:**
```html
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="Style.css">
  <!-- Other meta tags and links -->
</head>
```
**Note:** Make sure the `Style.css` file is in the same directory as your HTML files or adjust the `href` path accordingly.

