message.content:
**Theme Toggle Button:**
Add the following line within the `<body>` of your `index.html`, ideally before the closing `</body>` tag or in a suitable location based on your layout preferences:

```html
<button id="theme-toggle">Toggle Theme</button>
```

**JavaScript File (e.g., `script.js`):**
Create a new file named `script.js` in the same directory as your `index.html` and `Style.css`. Add the following code to this file:

```javascript
// script.js

// Select the theme toggle button
const themeToggle = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');

// Define the theme classes
const DARK_THEME_CLASS = 'dark-theme';
const LIGHT_THEME_CLASS = 'light-theme';

// Initial theme check ( defaults to light if no class is found )
let currentTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || LIGHT_THEME_CLASS;

// Apply the initial theme (if stored in local storage)
document.body.classList.add(currentTheme);

// Toggle theme function
function toggleTheme() {
  // Check the current theme and switch to the other one
  if (currentTheme === LIGHT_THEME_CLASS) {
    document.body.classList.replace(LIGHT_THEME_CLASS, DARK_THEME_CLASS);
    currentTheme = DARK_THEME_CLASS;
  } else {
    document.body.classList.replace(DARK_THEME_CLASS, LIGHT_THEME_CLASS);
    currentTheme = LIGHT_THEME_CLASS;
  }

  // Store the new theme in local storage
  localStorage.setItem('theme', currentTheme);
}

// Add event listener to the theme toggle button
themeToggle.addEventListener('click', toggleTheme);
```

**Linking the JavaScript File:**
Finally, link the `script.js` file to your `index.html` by adding the following line within the `<head>` section or before the closing `</body>` tag:

```html
<script src="script.js"></script>
```

**How It Works:**

1. **Initial Theme Detection:** The script checks for a stored theme in local storage, defaulting to the light theme if none is found.
2. **Theme Application:** Applies the detected (or default) theme to the `<body>` element.
3. **Toggle Mechanism:** When the toggle button is clicked, the script swaps the current theme class with the alternative one on the `<body>` element.
4. **Storage Update:** The newly selected theme is stored in local storage for persistence across page reloads.

**Note:** This implementation uses `localStorage` to store the user's preferred theme, ensuring the selection persists even after the browser is closed and reopened.

